{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "Ironically today that  use-case is now de-favored by the algorithm.  Heavily.  So you have to jump through hoops to share links.   If you want anyone to see them, that is.", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481395028033926", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:02 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 9, "view_count": "1150", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "I\u2019m not a huge Web 3.0 guy, but I\u2019ve been reading Chris Dixon\u2019s \u201cRead, Write Own\u201d and his analysis of \u201cwhat went wrong\u201d with the Internet is spot on. \n\nI\u2019m not all sure that Web 3.0 fixes all those problems, but the problems are real.", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481403823558847", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:04 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 11, "view_count": "1438", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "This is not some general nihilism.  It\u2019s a property of social media.  First the early adopters come and with a vision.  Then some breakthrough happens and it takes off.  Then everyone comes.  Then it gets ruined.", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481392406598053", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:01 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 7, "view_count": "1281", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "I went on Facebook hiatus several years ago.  \n\nThe trigger event was that I found myself in an argument with a moron from my high school.  An argument, btw, that I was very politely trying to not have.  \n\nI asked myself:  why I am spending my time this way?  Is this a good use", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481405379563848", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:05 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 10, "view_count": "1584", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "Put differently.  I didn\u2019t change.  The site changed on me.  I still wanted to do the use-case I\u2019ve always done.  But the site isn\u2019t about that use-case anymore.\n\nDance with who brung ya. \n\nI\u2019m sure some other site will come along and do that, so is the Silicon Valley cycle of", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481401826971753", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:04 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 7, "view_count": "1237", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "I saw a post on Instagram the other day.  \n\nThe person was saying:  I used this site to keep in touch with my friends.  To see updates on them and their kids.  Now I can\u2019t find those updates.  The more the site became \u201centertainment,\u201d the more I got sucked into viral videos,", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481400426131618", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:03 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 5, "view_count": "1286", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "Social media is a tragedy of the commons.  For that matter, so is the Internet.  The trend seems to be that it gets ruined over time.\n\nI remember using eBay back when people always paid, would come to my house to pick up items.", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481391207022991", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:01 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 9, "view_count": "1274", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "The deterioration is two-sided.\n\nNot only is it harder to share things that people will find, it\u2019s harder to find things that I want to share.\n\nSo my two use-cases were:\n1. Share my content.  Now harder and less effective.\n2. Find interesting things to read.  Now harder and less", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481396609303039", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:02 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 11, "view_count": "1276", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "For Twitter, I think the breakthrough was link-shortening.  Unlike Delicious, which was cumbersome to use, Twitter became an easy way to share links to interesting things.  \n\nCasting URLs as messages in bottles beat social bookmarking.", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481393753039191", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:02 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 9, "view_count": "1203", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "Some of this is a crisis of measurement.\n\nI never understood why \u201cengagement\u201d mattered so much to social media companies.  (I also never really understood \u201cgetting ratioed.\u201d )\n\nIf you view Twitter as a link-sharing site, the dominant metric should be links pressed.  \n\nBut likes", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481398001873244", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:03 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "favorite_count": 6, "view_count": "1311", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
{"username": "Kellblog", "name": "Dave Kellogg", "text": "And never came back.  And don\u2019t miss it.  \n\nI don\u2019t know how my Twitter/X hiatus will end.  I\u2019ve really enjoyed the site over the years.  I thank all of you who\u2019ve followed me, and engaged with me.  \n\nI\u2019ve found new friends and new companies here.\n\nI\u2019m just no confident that will", "lang": "en", "in_reply_to": "1820481407262830810", "is_quote_status": false, "retweeted_tweet": null, "possibly_sensitive": null, "favorited": false, "date": "Mon Aug 05 15:26:05 +0000 2024", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 4, "favorite_count": 17, "view_count": "2064", "view_count_state": "EnabledWithCount", "retweet_count": 0, "place": null, "is_translatable": false, "edits_remaining": "5", "has_card": false, "thumbnail_title": null, "urls": [], "hashtags": []}
